stylometry: The decision theory is when a decision maker has to decide on certain things while weighing the possible outcomes of each in order to find the best solution available. There are three components. 1. A set of decisions or startegies is made aware to the decision maker. 2. The decision maker is aware of the outcomes and probabilities of the outcomes. 3. A value model shows monetary values and the decisions made the the decision maker. They're related because both of them need to be able to decide on a strategy and then become aware of the possible outcomes of the decision.
